article.headline: Henderson scores 23 to lead Niagara over Mount St. Mary's 82-71
article.description: — Ahmad Henderson II's 23 points helped Niagara defeat Mount St. Mary's 82-71 on Sunday.
article.linkText: Henderson scores 23 to lead Niagara over Mount St. Mary's 82-71
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- — Ahmad Henderson II's 23 points helped Niagara defeat Mount St. Mary's 82-71 on Sunday. Henderson was 7 of 15 shooting, including 3 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 7 from the line for the Purple Eagles (9-9, 5-3 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Kwane Marble II finished 6 of 7 from the field to add 13 points. Randy Tucker was 4 of 5 shooting (3 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points. The Mountaineers (7-11, 3-4) were led by Dakota Leffew, who posted 18 points. Dallas Hobbs added 12 points for Mount St. Mary's. Ron Jessamy also put up eight points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
